    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large bells, often in a set of bells, hung in the tower of a church and rung for various purposes, including the following: to call people to worship services; to mark an event such as a wedding, funeral, festival, etc.; or to mark the hours of the day, in order to keep time for the community. For handbells used at an altar in a church, use "altar bells."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
